   <abstract>Collection of texts on Shiʻī law, mostly by Aḥmad ibn Ibrāhīm al-Baḥrānī (d. 1719), written by the same hand</abstract>
   <note>Ms. codex</note>
   <note type="titleSrc">Title supplied by cataloger</note>
   <note type="physicalDetails">21 to 22 lines per page. Fol. 249b-292b: 12 lines per page. Most texts are written in small naskh in black ink, apparently by the same hand. European glazed paper
      with watermark. Fol. 1 is a fly-leaf, with inscription. Ownership statements on fol. 2a. Foliation in pencil using Western numerals</note>
   <note>There are several notes which mention that these texts were copied at the request of Jaʻfar Muḥammad Kāẓim in Mashhad Ḥusayn [Karbalāʼ] in 1239 (see fol. 2a, with seal), 1234 (fol. 63a, 77a),
      1236 (fol. 249a)</note>
   <note type="provenance">Acquired from Abraham Shalom Yahuda, 1942</note>
   <note type="bindingInfo">Upper and lower covers made of clear brown leather over paper pasteboards, with two blind-tooled fillets encompassing an inner border made of a single blind-tooled
      fillet</note>
   <note type="contents">1. fol. 2b-52a: al-Fawāʼid al-Ḥāʼirīyah / Muḥammad Bāqir Bahbahānī (d. 1791 or 2)</note>
   <note type="contents">2. fol. 52b-54b: [Blank]</note>
   <note type="contents">3. fol. 55a-61a: Risālah fī al-istiṣḥāb / Muḥammad Bāqir Bahbahānī (d. 1791 or 2)</note>
   <note type="contents">4. fol. 61b-62b: [Blank]</note>
   <note type="contents">5. fol. 63a-77a: Risālat Muqaddimat al-wājib / Muḥammad Sharīf Mazandarānī (d. 1829 or 30)</note>
